# Semi-structured & nested JSON

The card feed is nested JSON (`card`, `merchant`, `auth` sub-objects). Two options:

- **Land nested, flatten in silver** (the exam's pick) — Auto Loader infers `STRUCT`/`ARRAY<STRUCT>`; bronze keeps it nested, silver flattens. Keeps original shape + replay
- **Land flat at the source** — cleaner downstream, but you lose the shape

## Three primitives to memorise

- **Dot access** — `df.select("merchant.name")` on `STRUCT` fields
- **`explode(arr)`** — one row per array element
- **`from_json(str, schema)`** — parse a JSON string into a struct (turns `_rescued_data` typed)

For one object spread across lines, use **`multiLine = true`** (an Auto Loader `json` format option).
